# Bootstrap Paragraph Guard

Bootstrap applies `p { margin-bottom: 1rem }` globally.

To prevent layout gaps in Bootstrap-based host apps:
- every `<p>` in component source must include one of:
  - `m-0`
  - `mb-0`
  - `my-0`

This applies to:
- inline `className` strings on `<p>`
- CVA base class strings used by `<p>` elements

Before shipping or publishing:

```bash
node scripts/check-bootstrap-compat.js
```

The Cursor dev workflow plugin also installs a hook that blocks matching:
- `git commit`
- `git push`
- `npm publish`
- `npm version`

when the Bootstrap compatibility scan fails.
